, 1949-Sept. 9, 1949; Annibale F. Verzumo, Sept. 16, 1949-Jan. 16, 1953; C. Ferri, Jan. 30, 1953-<Nov., 1953>.", "Vol. 15, no. 1 (Jan. 5, 1951) misdated Dec. 5, 1950.", "No issues published Feb. 1-Mar. 28, 1952.", "\"Italian-American weekly,\" <1942>-Sept. 8, 1949; May 23-<Nov., 1953>.", "In Italian with occasional articles in English.", "Description based on: Vol. 5, no. 49 (Dec. 4, 1942)."], "number": ["00516993923", "1", "sn83035602"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn83035602"], "number_reel": ["00516993923"], "numeric_shelf_id": 194509141, "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_formats": [{"label": "MODSXML Record", "link": "//tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp//ohi/batch_ohi_hagrid_ver01/data/sn83035602/00516993923/1945091401/1945091401_1.xml"}, {"label": "MARCXML Record", "link": "//lccn.loc.gov/sn83035602/marcxml"}], "other_title": ["Herald"], "partof": [{"count": 565, "title": "l'araldo = the herald (cleveland, ohio) 1938-1959", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:l%27araldo+%3D+the+herald+%28cleveland,+ohio%29+1938-1959&fo=json"}, {"count": 3203926, "title": "chronicling america", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/chronicling-america/?fo=json"}, {"count": 3225157, "title": "serial and government publications division", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:serial+and+government+publications+division&fo=json"}], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["l'araldo = the herald (cleveland, ohio) 1938-1959"], "place_of_publication": "Cleveland, Ohio", "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "raw_lccn": "sn 83035602 ", "reel_numbers": ["00516993923"], "resources": [{"files": 16, "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ohi:batch_ohi_hagrid_ver01:data:sn83035602:00516993923:1945091401:0308/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83035602/1945-09-14/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.45633, "shard": "04", "shelf_id": "sn83035602, 1945-09-14, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/ohi", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["newspapers", "cleveland", "cuyahoga", "ohio", "italians", "italian", "united states"], "subject_ethnicity": ["italian"], "subject_headings": ["Italians--Ohio--Newspapers", "Italians", "Ohio", "United States--Ohio--Cuyahoga--Cleveland"], "subjects": [{"cleveland": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:cleveland&fo=json"}, {"cuyahoga": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:cuyahoga&fo=json"}, {"italian": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:italian&fo=json"}, {"italians": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:italians&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"ohio": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:ohio&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "subjects_ethnicity": [{"italian": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject_ethnicity:italian&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2025-04-13T10:57:57.185Z", "title": "L'araldo = The Herald (Cleveland, Ohio), September 14, 1945", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83035602/1945-09-14/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83035602/"], "batch": ["ohi_hagrid_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1938", "description": ["Weekly Began in 1938; ceased in 1959. Cf. Veronesi, G.P. Italian Amers. and their communities in Clev., 1977. Publisher: L'Araldo Pub. Co., <1942>-Feb. 1, 1952; Louis de Paolo, Mar. 29, 1952-Jan. 16, 1953; L'Araldo Pub. Co., Jan. 23, 1953-<Nov., 1953>. Editors: Matteo Teresi, <1942>-Jan. 14, 1949; Igino N. Ceraldi, Jan. 21, 1949-Sept. 9, 1949; Annibale F. Verzumo, Sept. 16, 1949-Jan. 16, 1953; C. Ferri, Jan. 30, 1953-<Nov., 1953>. Vol. 15, no. 1 (Jan. 5, 1951) misdated Dec. 5, 1950. No issues published Feb. 1-Mar. 28, 1952. \"Italian-American weekly,\" <1942>-Sept. 8, 1949; May 23-<Nov., 1953>. In Italian with occasional articles in English. Description based on: Vol. 5, no. 49 (Dec. 4, 1942)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:13.325Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83035602/", "image_url": [], "index": 13, "language": ["italian", "english"], "latlong": [41.5051414, -81.6914575], "location": ["cleveland", "cuyahoga county", "ohio", "cuyahoga", "united states"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-81.6914575, 41.5051414], "number": ["online resource", "2025-04-13t02:20:28.043698", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83035602/1942-12-04/ed-1/", "microfilm service copy", "10094919", "western rsv hist soc, newsp proj", "564", "unspecified", "ohio hist soc", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83035602/1953-11-20/ed-1/", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "1", "sn83035602"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Herald"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "l'araldo = the herald (cleveland, ohio) 1938-1959", "serial and government publications division", "chronicling america"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 56.977646, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83035602", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd"], "subject": ["cleveland (ohio)", "newspapers", "italian americans", "cuyahoga county (ohio)", "cleveland", "cuyahoga", "ohio", "italians", "italian", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:07:48.184Z", "title": "L'araldo = The Herald", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83035602/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220118/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1854", "dates": ["[1854 TO 1865]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sunday) Print began with v. 8, no. 2503 (Mar. 16, 1854); ceased with Vol. XIX, No. 103 (April 29, 1865) Republican. Daily evening ed.: Cleveland evening leader, <>-1865. Vol. 12, No. 131 (June 1, 1858); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Feb. 8, 2021). Vol. XIX, No. 103 (April 29, 1865) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Feb. 8, 2021). Cleveland leader (Cleveland, Ohio : 1865 : Online) 2327-1361 (DLC) 2013218612 (OCoLC)829112638"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:17.248Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220118/", "image_url": [], "index": 14, "language": ["english"], "location": ["cleveland", "cuyahoga county", "ohio", "cuyahoga", "united states"], "number": ["online resource", "778030732", "2021220118", "2013218612", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2767-1348"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Cleveland leader", "Daily leader"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "cleveland morning leader (cleveland [ohio]) 1854-1865 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 35.06342, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD AP3 .C54", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["cleveland (ohio)", "newspapers", "cleveland", "cuyahoga county", "ohio", "cuyahoga county (ohio)", "cuyahoga", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "Cleveland morning leader", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220118/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018270596/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["south slavic socialist labor party federation", "petrovich, lazar", "slepcevich, peter"], "date": "1907", "dates": ["[1907 TO 1970]"], "description": ["Semimonthly, July 14, 1966-1970 Began with Sept. 19, 1907 issue; ceased Oct. 8, 1970. Imprint varies: 1907-1910 published in New York; 1910-1943 published in Cleveland; 1943-1970 published in Detroit. Editors: Lazar Petrovich, <1919>-1926, 1948-1957; Peter Slepcevich, <1958-1967>. Also issued on microfilm from the Library of Congress Photoduplication Service and the New York Public Library. In Serbo-Croatian (Roman) with some columns in English. Official organ of the: South Slavic Socialist Labor Party Federation. Description based on: Vol. XXXIV, No. 3 (January 16, 1941); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 19, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XXXIX, No. 3 (January 17, 1946) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 19, 2018)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:46.349Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018270596/", "image_url": [], "index": 15, "language": ["croatian", "english"], "location": ["michigan", "detroit", "wayne", "cleveland", "new york", "cuyahoga", "ohio", "new york city", "united states"], "number": ["1079422283", "online resource", "2641-0168", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2018270596"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Workers' struggle"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "radni\u010dka borba = workers' struggle (cleveland, o.) 1907-1970 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["semimonthly"], "score": 35.06342, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["new york (state)", "michigan", "cleveland (ohio)", "yugoslavs", "detroit", "wayne", "cleveland", "new york", "ohio", "newspapers", "new york (n.y.)", "cuyahoga", "detroit (mich.)", "yugoslavian", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:57:39.303Z", "title": "Radnic\u030cka borba = Workers' struggle", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018270596/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2019218562/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2019218562", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/2f93aa86-bad9-594d-b59d-bef113d86d45"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1961", "dates": ["[1961 TO 9999]"], "description": ["Daily Began September 16, 1961. Published: Cleveland, Ohio, September 16, 1961- Publisher: Forest City Pub. Co., September 16, 1961- Suspended: Nov. 30, 1962-Apr. 8, 1963, and: Nov. 2-Dec. 21, 1974 due to strikes. Also issued on microfilm from University Microfilms International. Description based on: July 3, 2018 (surrogate); title from masthead. Latest issue consulted: July 3, 2018 (surrogate)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:01.189Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-04", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-04"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2019218562/", "image_url": [], "index": 16, "language": ["english"], "location": ["cleveland", "cuyahoga county", "ohio", "cuyahoga", "united states"], "number": ["online resource", "2641-4058", "2025-07-01t13:40:55.900000", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "137347175", "2019218562"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Sunday issues for <May 15, 1994-> published as: Sunday plain dealer"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "the plain dealer (brooklyn, oh) 1961-current [online resource]", "catalog"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 35.06342, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["cleveland (ohio)", "periodicals", "newspapers", "cleveland", "cuyahoga county", "ohio", "cuyahoga county (ohio)", "cuyahoga", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:57:55.117Z", "title": "The plain dealer", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2019218562/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218665/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["haupt, herman g.", "mosler, joseph", "rosenberg, w. l.", "frebe, fritz", "jodlbauer, joseph"], "date": "1911", "dates": ["[1911 TO 1920]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. 1, no. 1 (April 29, 1911); ceased with IX. Jahrgang, no. 52 (April 17, 1920). Published on Saturday. Publishers: Vereinigten Deutschen Socialisten der S.B. Clevelands, Apr. 29, 1911-Feb. 1, 1913; Deutsche Staats-Agitations-Komitee fu\u0308r Ohio, Feb. 8, 1913-Apr. 17, 1920. With Feb. 8, 1913 issue, the subtitle changed to: Wochenblatt des Deutschen Socialisten des Staates Ohio. \"Socialist.\" Cf. Gutgesell, S. Guide to Ohio newspapers, 1974. Editors: W.L. Rosenberg, Apr. 29, 1911-Mar. 10, 1912; Jos. Jodlbauer, Mar. 16, 1912-Aug. 28, 1915; Jos. Mosler, Sept. 4, 1915-<Apr.27, 1917>; Fritz Frebe, <Dec. 21, 1918-Oct. 25, 1919>; Herman G. Haupt, <Dec. 13, 1919>-Apr. 17, 1920. In German. Officialles Organ der Deutschen Branches der Socialist Partei des Staates Ohio. Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 1 (April 29, 1911); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed March 28, 2018). Latest issue consulted: IX. Jahrgang, no. 52 (April 17, 1920) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed March 28, 2018)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:42.357Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218665/", "image_url": [], "index": 17, "language": ["german"], "location": ["ohio", "cleveland", "united states", "cuyahoga"], "number": ["1029740311", "online resource", "2577-4204", "2018218665", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["echo : wochenblatt der vereinigten deutschen socialisten clevelands (cleveland, o. [ohio]) 1911-1920 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 35.06342, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["cleveland (ohio)", "cleveland", "ohio", "newspapers", "cuyahoga", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:56:09.337Z", "title": "Echo : Wochenblatt der Vereinigten Deutschen Socialisten Clevelands", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218665/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218694/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1918", "dates": ["[1918 TO 1957]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sat., Sun., and holidays), Dec. 10, 1945-Apr. 1, 1957 Began April 6, 1918; ceased April 1, 1957. Includes bibliographical references (Bajec, J. Slovensko izseljensko c\u030casopisje 1891-1945, Ljubljana, 1980). \"Neodvisen dnevnik za Slovenske delavce v Ameriki.\" In Slovenian and English. Description based 