interview with three members of the musical group Harmonia: Walt Mikhailovich, Alexander Fedoriouk, and Andrei Pidkivka, regarding learning folk and classical music and playing music as part of community life among Slavic Americans in Cleveland, Ohio and other cities and towns in the central and northeastern United States. They discuss their varied repertoire of older music and music of diverse ethnic groups including Hungarian, Slovak, Ukrainian, Romanian, Croatian, and Roma (Gypsy) music. Group members were interviewed by Theadocia Austen following Harmonia's performance in the Library's Coolidge Auditorium as part of the American Folklife Center's Homegrown concert series."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2020-09-20T06:24:10.711Z", "group": ["songamerica", "catalog-split-07", "catalog", "songs-of-america-afc", "main-catalog-split-07", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014655547/", "image_url": [], "index": 17, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [41.52, -81.5561111111], "location": ["cleveland", "eastern europe", "ohio", "slavic countries"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-81.5561111111, 41.52], "mime_type": ["application/x-video"], "number": ["2015-08-04t15:56:55", "2014655547"], "online_format": ["video"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "other_title": ["Oral history with Harmonia band"], "partof": ["american folklife center", "the library of congress celebrates the songs of america", "catalog"], "score": 18.064768, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2014655547", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["slavic americans", "folk music", "europe, eastern", "interviews", "hungarian americans", "croatian americans", "harmonia (musical group)", "music", "cleveland", "ohio", "ukrainian americans", "musicians", "slavic countries"], "timestamp": "2022-03-28T20:31:06.692Z", "title": "Harmonia, an oral history interview with group members conducted by Theadocia Austen,", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2014655547/"}, {"access_r